  "prompt": "What was the first word spoken by a human being?",
  "response": "The exact first word spoken by a human being is not known, as language development predates written records by thousands of years. Early human communication likely began with simple sounds or gestures, gradually evolving into more complex forms of language. While there are theories about the origins of specific words, no definitive record exists to identify the very first word ever spoken. Linguists and anthropologists continue to study the evolution of language to better understand its beginnings.",
